<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Dual Turbocharger and Exhaust Tubing - Installation - Air Inlet Duct and
        Support Tubing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Air Inlet Duct and Support Tubing</title>
        <figure id="f3000341" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/J15026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger air inlet duct clamp</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air inlet duct and clamp onto turbocharger, leaving clamp loose enough to allow
                rotation of duct.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the air inlet duct bracket mounting bolt (M6 x 16) and tighten to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque air inlet duct clamp to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_53.xml" xrefid="E30003B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000340" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/J15027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger air inlet support tubing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Boost control tubing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet tubing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install turbocharger air inlet support tubing and boost control tubing at actuator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate oil inlet hole of each turbocharger assembly with clean engine oil, spinning
                compressor wheel several times to allow oil to reach bearings. Refill oil inlet hole prior to installing
                oil supply line.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new O-ring seal #208 onto the oil supply line at oil filter base port.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new O-ring seal #2 at each of the oil supply line turbocharger port fittings.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000339" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj15/J15001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger oil supply line</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Uncap oil supply port in oil filter housing and install turbocharger oil supply line and
                mounting bolt (M6 x 20). Tighten bolt to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread oil supply line onto each of the turbocharger port fittings and tighten fittings to
                the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_53.xml" xrefid="E30003B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields and covers after servicing engine. Make sure all tools,
                covers, loose parts and service equipment are removed from engine area after all work is complete.
            </para>
        </step1>
